Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesson 41 Training elephants\N\N训练大象\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.74,0:00:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.31,0:00:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At what point does the training of a captive wild elephant begin?\N\N到什么情况下,才能开始对捕来的野象进行训练?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.24,0:00:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,technique: n.  技术\N\NTwo main techniques have been used for training elephants,\N\N驯象有两种主要的方法,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.14,0:00:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which we may call respectively the tough and the gentle.\N\N我们分别称之为强硬法和温柔法.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.30,0:00:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The former method simply consists of setting an elephant to work,\N\N强硬法就是驱使象去干活,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.17,0:00:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and beating him until he does what is expected of him.\N\N把它打到顺从为止.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.09,0:00:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Apart from any moral considerations this is a stupid method of training,\N\N且不说道义问题,这本身就是一种愚蠢的训练方法,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.87,0:00:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for it produces a resentful animal who at a later stage may well turn man-killer.\N\N因为这种方法训练会使动物反感,在以后某个时期可能会变成伤人的动物.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The gentle method requires more patience in the early stages,\N\N温柔法要求在最初阶段保持较大的耐心,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.92,0:00:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but produce a cheerful good-tempered elephant who will give many years of loyal service.\N\N但这种方法可以训练出性情愉快,脾气温顺,能忠实为人服务多年的大象.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.36,0:01:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,assign: v.  分配，指派, mahout: n.  驯象人\N\NThe first essential in elephant training is to assign to the animal a single mahout,\N\N驯象中至关重要的是指派一名专门的驯象员,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.93,0:01:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who will be entirely responsible for the job.\N\N全面负责这项工作.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.93,0:01:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Elephants like to have one master just as dogs do,\N\N大象和狗一样,喜欢有一个专一的主人,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.10,0:01:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and are capable of a considerable degree of personal affection.\N\N而且会对主人产生相当深厚的私人感情.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.38,0:01:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There are even stories of half-trained elephant calves,\N\N甚至有这样的故事:训练了一半的小象,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.60,0:01:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,pine: v.  消瘦\N\Nwho have refused to feed and pined to death,\N\N拒绝吃食,消瘦至死,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.73,0:01:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when by some unavoida- ble circumstance they have been deprived of their own trainer.\N\N起因是由于不可避免的情况与它们的主人分离.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.35,0:01:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Such extreme cases must probably be taken with a grain of salt,\N\N这种极端的事例虽不可全信,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.64,0:01:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,underline: v.  着重说明，强调\N\Nbut they do underline the general principle:\N\N但强调了一项基本原则:\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.53,0:01:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,mahout: n.  驯象人\N\Nthat the relationship between elephant and mahout is the key to successful training.\N\N象和驯象员之间的关系是驯象成功与否的关键.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.40,0:01:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The most economical age to capture an elephant for training,\N\N捕捉大象进行驯练最经济的象龄,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is between 15 and 20 years,\N\N15至20岁之间,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.16,0:01:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for it is then almost ready to undertake heavy work,\N\N这个年龄的象差不多已能干重活,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.10,0:02:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,keep: n.  生计\N\Nand can begin to earn its keep straight away.\N\N可以很快挣回饲养它的开支.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.89,0:02:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But animals of this age do not easily become subservient to man,\N\N但这个年龄的象不易驯服,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.38,0:02:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very firm hand must be employed in the early stages.\N\N因此开始阶段需要有一位强有力的老手.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.95,0:02:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The captive elephant, still roped to a tree,\N\N捕来拴在树上的大象,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.63,0:02:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,plunges and screams every time a man approaches,\N\N每当有人走近它时,就会向前猛冲并发出尖叫,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and for several days will probably refuse all food through anger and fear.\N\N甚至一连几天由于愤怒和恐惧而拒绝进食.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes a tame elephant is tethered nearby to give the wild one confidence.\N\N有时,把一头已驯服的象拴在旁边能给野象以信心.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.01,0:02:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and in most cases the captive gradually qui- etens down and begins to accept its food.\N\N在大多数情况下,刚捕来的象会慢慢静下来,接着开始吃食.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The next stage is to get the elephant to the training establishment,\N\N下一步就是把象带到训练场所,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.88,0:02:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a ticklish business which is achieved,\N\N这是一件棘手的事,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.59,0:02:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with the aid of two tame elephants roped to the captive on either side.\N\N需要在它两侧拴上两头驯服的大象帮忙才能完成.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.56,0:02:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When several elephants are being trained at one time,\N\N几只象同时训练时,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.39,0:02:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it is customary for the new arrival to be placed,\N\N通常是把新到的安置在,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.00,0:03:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,between the stalls of two captives whose training is already well advanced.\N\N两头训练得很好的大象的象厩中间.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.75,0:03:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It is then left completely undisturbed with plenty of food and water,\N\N然后给它以充足的食物和水,一定不要惊扰它,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.60,0:03:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it can absorb the atmosphere of its new home,\N\N以便让它能适应新居的气氛,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.11,0:03:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that nothing particularly alarming is happening to its companions.\N\N并且看到自己的同伴身上没有发生让自己担惊受怕的事.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.67,0:03:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When it is eating normally,its own training begins.\N\N当它进食正常了,训练就开始.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.14,0:03:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The trainer stands in front of the elephant\N\N驯练员站在象前\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,holding a long stick with a sharp metal point.\N\N手持一根有锋利金属尖头的长棒.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.25,0:03:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Two assistants,mounted on tame elephants, control the captive from either side,\N\N两位助手骑在驯服的象的背上,从两侧控制新捕的象,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.17,0:03:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,while others rub their hands over his skin\N\N其他人一边用手抚摸象的皮肤,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.20,0:03:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,accompaniment: n.  伴奏, chant: n.  单调的歌\N\Nto the accompaniment of a monotonous and soothing chant.\N\N一边唱着单调的歌安抚它.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is supposed to induce pleasurable sensations in the elephant,\N\N据说这是为了使象产生愉快的感觉,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.72,0:03:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,reinforce: v.  加强, epithet: n.  称呼\N\Nand its effects are reinforced by the use of endearing epithets,\N\N为了加强这种效果,人们还给以大象以亲切的外号\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.46,0:03:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,such as'ho!my son',or 'ho! my father',or 'my mother',\N\N如"嗬!我的孩子"、"嗬!我的爸爸"、"嗬!我的妈妈".\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the age and sex of the captive\N\N这些外号是按象的年龄性别来给的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.68,0:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,blandishment: n.  奉承\N\NThe elephant is not immediately susceptible to such blandishments,however,\N\N然而大象不会立刻被这些讨好的话感动,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.01,0:04:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,lash: v.  猛烈地甩\N\Nand usually lashes fiercely with its trunk in all directions.\N\N而往往是用鼻子朝各个方向猛烈地甩动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.02,0:04:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These movements are controlled by the trainer with the metal-pointed stick,\N\N训练员要用有锋利金属尖的长棒控制它的这种举动\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.02,0:04:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and the trunk eventually becomes so sore that the elephant curls it up\N\N象鼻子最后疼得卷了起来,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.87,0:04:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and seldom afterwards uses it for offensive purposes.\N\N以后它就很少用鼻子去进攻了.\N\N